        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-04 05:42:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> The commit message looks good overall! However, here are some minor suggestions:\n> \n> * **Consistency:** While 'SPDX' is capitalized in the subject line, it's written as lowercase ('spdx') in the description. Choose one style and stick to it for consistency. Consider updating the description to also use 'SPDX'.\n\nThis is wrong? Amusingly, it misses the typo i.e. `spdx`.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0e3ef34d3dc63a25900458ad485f93fd6255a1c4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-04 05:58:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > The commit message looks good overall! However, here are some minor suggestions:\n> > \n> > * **Consistency:** While 'SPDX' is capitalized in the subject line, it's written as lowercase ('spdx') in the description. Choose one style and stick to it for consistency. Consider updating the description to also use 'SPDX'.\n> \n> This is wrong? Amusingly, it misses the typo i.e. `spdx`.\n\nWell, as you can probably see, I am playing with LLMs to evaluate commit messages, though the results have been a lot less repeatable than I hoped.\nAt first in dryrun it noticed the typo and had no other comments, so I run it in the \"post\" mode and of course due to a different seed it decided it'll have a brainfart and would miss the  typo, but imagine a problem that is not there.\n\nI guess I'll keep narrovign various prompts and see if this could stil be done in automatic mode or if I'll have to resort to manual runs. Or may be I need a DGX or two so I can run really large ones that are bound to be better, right? right?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
